    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-16T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-16T23:00:00-05:00" n="399"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4–1746: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Mukden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mukden</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-17T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 17, 1946—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 9:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>31. Am informed (ReConstel April 9, 9 a.m.<note n="15" xml:id="d399fn15">Not
                        printed.</note> penultimate paragraph) that Chinese on April 11 obtained
                    control Fushun mine from Soviets.</p>
                <p>Whether this recovery was unqualified is still unclear.</p>
                <p>Please repeat Chungking, Shanghai.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
